{
  "stem": "812.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "It was-- ordinarily, it would have taken maybe nine to 10 hours to get to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But because the Germans tried to evade the Allies, we were on this train for almost two weeks.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And the trains-- the train would come to a stop every so often.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We were allowed, those who were able to, get off and take a little water from a stream.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "My mother would collect a little water from a locomotive.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And that's how we got our drink.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "As far as hunger, I know that we-- we didn't feel that anymore.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But thirst and sleep was always needed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Drink was needed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "This train was heading, as I said, towards Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And it was towards the end of our trip-- was-- that the Germans stormed through the train and demanded civilian clothing, our civilian clothing.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "We then knew that the war was coming towards an end.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "While on the train, there were constant bombings and constant planes and shootings and whatnot.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "We never knew whether we would be hit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And even if we did, so probably would have been just as well.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "There came a time where we really did not care to go on anymore and didn't think that it-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that that-- that we would survive.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And yet, deep down, I personally always felt that things had to get just a little bit worse before they can get better.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And I always said, as long as we can see and as long as we are alive, there is that hope.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And my mother was always consoling us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And we were always talking about what will be after we were liberated.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
